---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Green Energy: The Real Story vs Marketing Nonsense | Texas Guide 2024";
const description = "Want actual green energy in Texas? Learn what's really green vs marketing greenwashing. Don't pay extra for fake environmental benefits.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-b from-texas-cream to-gray-50">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <div class="bg-texas-navy text-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
          Green Energy: The Real Story
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-blue-100 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          Here's the truth: Texas actually has tons of wind and solar power, so "green" energy isn't just feel-good marketing here. But companies love to slap "green" on plans and charge you extra for basically nothing. Let me show you what's actually green and what's just expensive marketing.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <span class="bg-texas-red px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">10 min read</span>
          <span class="bg-texas-gold px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-medium text-texas-navy">Eco-Friendly</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
      <!-- Green Stats -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-600 mb-2">#1</div>
          <div class="text-gray-600">State in renewable energy production</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-600 mb-2">37%</div>
          <div class="text-gray-600">Of Texas electricity from renewables</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-600 mb-2">100%</div>
          <div class="text-gray-600">Green plans available from 80+ providers</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <div class="space-y-12">
        <section class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-texas-navy mb-6">Understanding Green Energy in Texas</h2>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-texas-navy mb-4">Texas Renewable Energy Overview</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                Texas generates more renewable energy than any other state, primarily from wind and solar. The state's deregulated electricity market allows you to choose providers that source energy from renewable sources.
              </p>
              
              <div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg mb-4">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Texas Renewable Energy Mix (2024)</h4>
                <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-green-700">
                  <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Wind Energy:</span><span>28% of total generation</span></div>
                  <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Solar Energy:</span><span>6% of total generation</span></div>
                  <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Hydroelectric:</span><span>1% of total generation</span></div>
                  <div class="flex justify-between"><span>Biomass:</span><span>2% of total generation</span></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-texas-navy mb-4">How Green Plans Work</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Renewable Energy Certificates (RECs)</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                    Most green plans use RECs to offset your electricity usage. For every kWh you use, your provider retires a REC from renewable energy generation.
                  </p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Direct Renewable Sourcing</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                    Some providers directly purchase electricity from wind and solar farms, ensuring your power comes from renewable sources.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-texas-navy mb-6">Types of Green Energy Plans</h2>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div class="space-y-6">
              <div class="border border-green-300 rounded-lg p-6 bg-green-50">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-green-700 mb-3">100% Renewable Plans</h3>
                <p class="text-green-700 mb-3">
                  Every kWh of your usage is matched with renewable energy certificates or direct renewable generation.
                </p>
                <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-green-600">
                  <div class="flex items-center"><span class="text-green-600 mr-2">âœ“</span>Complete carbon neutrality</div>
                  <div class="flex items-center"><span class="text-green-600 mr-2">âœ“</span>Maximum environmental impact</div>
                  <div class="flex items-center"><span class="text-orange-600 mr-2">~</span>Typically 1-3Â¢/kWh premium</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="border border-blue-300 rounded-lg p-6 bg-texas-cream-200">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-texas-navy mb-3">Partial Renewable Plans</h3>
                <p class="text-texas-navy mb-3">
                  50-99% of your usage matched with renewable energy, with the remainder from traditional sources.
                </p>
                <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-texas-navy">
                  <div class="flex items-center"><span class="text-green-600 mr-2">âœ“</span>Lower cost than 100% plans</div>
                  <div class="flex items-center"><span class="text-green-600 mr-2">âœ“</span>Still significant environmental benefit</div>
                  <div class="flex items-center"><span class="text-texas-navy mr-2">~</span>Usually 0.5-1.5Â¢/kWh premium</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-6">
              <div class="border border-purple-300 rounded-lg p-6 bg-purple-50">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-purple-700 mb-3">Solar-Specific Plans</h3>
                <p class="text-purple-700 mb-3">
                  Plans that specifically source renewable energy from solar farms and installations.
                </p>
                <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-purple-600">
                  <div class="flex items-center"><span class="text-green-600 mr-2">âœ“</span>Support solar energy development</div>
                  <div class="flex items-center"><span class="text-green-600 mr-2">âœ“</span>Often includes solar buyback programs</div>
                  <div class="flex items-center"><span class="text-purple-600 mr-2">~</span>May have time-of-use rates</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="border border-teal-300 rounded-lg p-6 bg-teal-50">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-teal-700 mb-3">Carbon Offset Plans</h3>
                <p class="text-teal-700 mb-3">
                  Traditional electricity plans that include carbon offset programs to neutralize environmental impact.
                </p>
                <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-teal-600">
                  <div class="flex items-center"><span class="text-green-600 mr-2">âœ“</span>Lower cost than renewable plans</div>
                  <div class="flex items-center"><span class="text-green-600 mr-2">âœ“</span>Support reforestation and clean projects</div>
                  <div class="flex items-center"><span class="text-orange-600 mr-2">~</span>Less direct renewable energy support</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-texas-navy mb-6">Cost Analysis: Are Green Plans Worth It?</h2>
          
          <div class="mb-8">
            <div class="bg-texas-cream-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-texas-navy mb-3">ðŸ’¡ Good News: Green Plans Are More Affordable Than Ever</h3>
              <p class="text-texas-navy">
                The cost difference between green and traditional plans has dramatically decreased. Many 100% renewable plans are now competitive with standard electricity rates.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2">12.8Â¢</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Average traditional plan rate</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="bg-green-100 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">13.5Â¢</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-green-600">Average 100% renewable plan</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="bg-texas-cream p-6 rounded-lg">
                <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-texas-navy mb-2">$8</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-texas-navy">Extra monthly cost (1,000 kWh)</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-yellow-800 mb-3">ðŸ“Š Environmental Impact Calculator</h3>
            <p class="text-yellow-800 mb-4">
              Switching to a 100% renewable plan for an average Texas home (1,200 kWh/month) prevents approximately:
            </p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm text-yellow-800">
              <div class="text-center">
                <div class="text-xl font-bold">12,000 lbs</div>
                <div>CO2 emissions annually</div>
              </div>
              <div class="text-center">
                <div class="text-xl font-bold">Equivalent to</div>
                <div>Planting 136 trees</div>
              </div>
              <div class="text-center">
                <div class="text-xl font-bold">Or removing</div>
                <div>1 car from roads for 3 months</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-texas-navy mb-6">Choosing the Right Green Plan</h2>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-green-700 mb-4">âœ… What to Look For</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Certification & Verification</h4>
                  <ul class="text-sm text-green-600 space-y-1">
                    <li>â€¢ Green-e certified renewable energy</li>
                    <li>â€¢ EPA Green Power Partner status</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Detailed renewable energy sourcing</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Transparent Pricing</h4>
                  <ul class="text-sm text-green-600 space-y-1">
                    <li>â€¢ Clear rate structure without gimmicks</li>
                    <li>â€¢ No hidden green energy fees</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Competitive total cost per kWh</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Additional Benefits</h4>
                  <ul class="text-sm text-green-600 space-y-1">
                    <li>â€¢ Solar panel buyback programs</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Energy efficiency tools and tips</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Carbon footprint tracking</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-red-700 mb-4">ðŸš¨ Red Flags to Avoid</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-700 mb-2">Greenwashing</h4>
                  <ul class="text-sm text-texas-red space-y-1">
                    <li>â€¢ Vague environmental claims</li>
                    <li>â€¢ No third-party certification</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Marketing-heavy, substance-light</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-700 mb-2">Excessive Premiums</h4>
                  <ul class="text-sm text-texas-red space-y-1">
                    <li>â€¢ More than 3Â¢/kWh above standard rates</li>
                    <li>â€¢ High monthly "environmental fees"</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Hidden costs for renewable energy</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-red-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-700 mb-2">Poor Contract Terms</h4>
                  <ul class="text-sm text-texas-red space-y-1">
                    <li>â€¢ Automatic conversion to non-green plans</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Unreasonable early termination fees</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Rate increases after promotional periods</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-texas-navy mb-6">Top Green Energy Providers in Texas</h2>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-texas-navy mb-4">Recommended Providers</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Green Mountain Energy</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">One of the pioneers in renewable energy retail, offers 100% renewable plans.</p>
                  <div class="text-xs text-gray-600">Specialties: Wind energy, pollution-free plans</div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Bulb Energy</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">UK-based provider focused on 100% renewable energy and carbon neutrality.</p>
                  <div class="text-xs text-gray-600">Specialties: Simple pricing, 100% renewable</div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
                  <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-700 mb-2">Rhythm Energy</h4>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-2">Texas-based provider with competitive renewable plans and smart home integration.</p>
                  <div class="text-xs text-gray-600">Specialties: Smart thermostats, renewable plans</div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-texas-navy mb-4">What to Compare</h3>
              <div class="bg-texas-cream-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-texas-navy mb-3">Provider Comparison Checklist</h4>
                <div class="space-y-2 text-sm text-texas-navy">
                  <label class="flex items-center">
                    <input type="checkbox" class="mr-3 text-green-600">
                    <span>Renewable energy percentage (50%, 100%)</span>
                  </label>
                  <label class="flex items-center">
                    <input type="checkbox" class="mr-3 text-green-600">
                    <span>Rate per kWh at your usage level</span>
                  </label>
                  <label class="flex items-center">
                    <input type="checkbox" class="mr-3 text-green-600">
                    <span>Monthly service fees</span>
                  </label>
                  <label class="flex items-center">
                    <input type="checkbox" class="mr-3 text-green-600">
                    <span>Contract length and flexibility</span>
                  </label>
                  <label class="flex items-center">
                    <input type="checkbox" class="mr-3 text-green-600">
                    <span>Third-party certifications</span>
                  </label>
                  <label class="flex items-center">
                    <input type="checkbox" class="mr-3 text-green-600">
                    <span>Customer reviews and ratings</span>
                  </label>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Footer CTA -->
      <div class="mt-16 text-center">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-green-600 to-green-800 text-white p-12 rounded-xl">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to Go Green?</h2>
          <p class="text-xl mb-8 text-green-100">Compare renewable energy plans and reduce your environmental impact today.</p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
            <a href="/electricity-plans" class="bg-white text-green-700 px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">
              Browse Green Plans
            </a>
            <a href="/rates/calculator" class="bg-texas-gold text-texas-navy px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-texas-gold-600 transition-colors">
              Calculate Green Energy Costs
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>